## üåæ Overview

Digital tools are transforming agriculture across Western Kenya. By combining mobile technology, AI, and data platforms, we empower farmers to make smarter decisions, reduce risk, and increase productivity.

---

## üì± Mobile Apps for Farmers

### <span class="fa-icon"><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i></span> Market Price Alerts
Real-time updates on commodity prices help farmers:
- Choose optimal selling times
- Avoid middlemen exploitation
- Coordinate with cooperatives for bulk sales

### <span class="fa-icon"><i class="fas fa-cloud-sun"></i></span> Weather Forecasts
Hyperlocal forecasts enable:
- Timely planting and harvesting
- Risk reduction from floods or droughts
- Planning irrigation and input use

### <span class="fa-icon"><i class="fas fa-virus"></i></span> Crop Disease Detection
AI-powered image recognition allows farmers to:
- Snap photos of affected crops
- Receive instant diagnosis and treatment tips
- Share findings with extension officers

---

## üßÆ Farmer Data Platforms

### <span class="fa-icon"><i class="fas fa-seedling"></i></span> Farm Productivity Tracking
Track inputs, yields, and seasonal trends to:
- Benchmark performance
- Identify inefficiencies
- Plan future investments

### <span class="fa-icon"><i class="fas fa-hand-holding-usd"></i></span> Access to Financial Services
Link farmers to:
- Microfinance institutions
- Crop insurance providers
- Digital wallets and payment systems

### <span class="fa-icon"><i class="fas fa-users"></i></span> Community Knowledge Sharing
Enable peer-to-peer learning through:
- Success stories and case studies
- Localized best practices
- Farmer forums and WhatsApp groups

